== Sweet Potato Fries ==

If you've decided to add sweet potato fries to your meal, preheat the #oven{} to 210°C.

Pop the @sweet potato fries{250%g} on a #baking tray{}, drizzle with @oil{} and season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

Toss to coat then spread out in a single layer and roast on the top shelf of your oven
until soft and golden, ~{18-20%minutes}, turning halfway.

> If you've added sweet potato fries to your recipe, serve on the side of your tacos and enjoy!

== Veggies ==

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @echalion shallot{1}.

Halve the @green pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 2cm sized chunks.

Drain and rinse the @sweetcorn{150%g} in a #sieve{}.

== Stir Fry ==

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once the oil is hot, add the pepper and sweetcorn.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, stir fry until the pepper has softened and the sweetcorn
has coloured slightly, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add the shallot to the pan with the veg, stir together and cook until the shallot is
soft too, ~{3-4%minutes}.

== Chipotle Mayo ==

Meanwhile, pop the @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} in a #bowl{} and add the @chipotle paste{10%g}.
Mix together and leave to the side.

Trim the @spring onion{1} and thinly slice.

== Halloumi ==

Once the veggies are soft, remove them to a bowl and pop your frying pan back on
medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

Add the @halloumi{250%g} to the pan and fry until golden brown on all sides,
~{5-6%minutes}. Turn every minute or so.

Meanwhile, pop your @plain taco tortillas{6} into the oven to warm through for
~{2-3%minutes}.

Once cooked, remove the pan from the heat.

== Assembly ==

Spread the chipotle mayo evenly on each of the tacos.

Divide the veg between the tacos and finish with some cubes of halloumi.

Sprinkle over the spring onion, serve with the sweet potato fries, enjoy!